:"Colas","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French/Haitian Pierre, Alain, Benoit, Christophe, Emile, Francoise, Fritz, Jean Daniel, Josseline, Luc, Monique, Remy.","French, West Indian (mainly Haiti), and Mauritian; Breton (rarely <b>Le Colas</b>); Spanish (<b>Colás</b>): from a short form of the personal name <i>Nicolas</i>, <i>Nicolás</i> (see   Nicolas   and   Nicholas  ). The surname of French and Breton origin was also brought to England by Huguenot refugees.","English (Yorkshire and Lancashire): variant of   Collis   (see also   Coles  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Nicolas","meanings":["From Late Greek.  See  <b>Nicholas</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1670184,"age":15,"year":"1598","julianDay":2304718,"title":"Edict of Nantes ","description":"Under the rule of Henry IV of France the Edict of Nantes was issued giving the people some religious liberty. The edict brought an end to the religious wars that were going on at the time. ","url":"https://www.britannica.com/event/Edict-of-Nantes","urlTitle":"Encyclopedia Britannica- Edict of Nantes","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1355839,"age":27,"year":"1610","julianDay":2309101,"description":"Reigns of Louis XIII and Louis XIV. Royal power at its peak. France dominates Europe, French culture spreads. Start of large-scale sea trade.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1670188,"age":35,"year":"1618","toYear":"1648","julianDay":2312023,"title":"30 Years War","description":"Ferdinand II was trying to force the people to follow Catholicism. The 30 years war was a battle of religion with the Protestants and Catholics, in the Holy Roman Empire.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/reformation/thirty-years-war","urlTitle":"History-Thirty Years' War","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Adam Jean Colas Grandadam was born about 1583, in Plaine, Bas-Rhin, France as the son of Jean Colin dit l'Homme Grandadam and Babillon NN. He ma